## Why are people switching from HockeyStack?

HockeyStack costs $2,200+/month and bundles everything together. You're here because you want B2B attribution without the all-in-one tax—or you need model flexibility to actually validate what's working.

### Quick Answer

**$2,200/mo too steep?** HockeyStack is priced for well-funded startups.
→ **Dreamdata** from $999/mo with a free tier to start
→ **mbuzz** at $29-299/mo for focused attribution

**Already have analytics tools?** HockeyStack bundles things you might not need.
→ **mbuzz** for attribution-only, integrate with your existing stack

**Need model flexibility?** HockeyStack gives you one view.
→ **mbuzz**—compare 8 models, validate with custom rules

**Enterprise Salesforce shop?** HockeyStack isn't the native choice.
→ **Bizible** (Adobe Marketo Measure)

### The Uncomfortable Truth

HockeyStack is fast to deploy and genuinely good at what it does. The problem? It's a bundle. You pay for web analytics, surveys, and attribution whether you need all three or not. And at $2,200+/month, that bundle adds up fast.

The bigger issue for serious B2B teams: you can't validate the attribution. HockeyStack says "LinkedIn drove this deal"—but you can't run a different model to check. You're trusting one black-box view of a 6-month sales cycle.

*If you want all-in-one simplicity and have the budget, HockeyStack delivers. This guide is for teams who want flexibility or lower cost.*

### Common Reasons to Switch

| Limitation | Impact |
|------------|--------|
| **Expensive** | $2,200+/mo starting, increasing with traffic |
| **All-in-one or nothing** | Bundled analytics you may not need |
| **No model flexibility** | Can't validate if attribution is accurate |
| **Vendor lock-in** | Deep integration makes switching costly |

If any of these resonate, here are your best options.

